<HEADLINE>
NATIONAL TAIWAN UNIVERSITY TURNS OUT MOST ARTICLES
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, May 12 (CNA) 05/13/07  10:07:13 (By Maubo Chang)
</P>
<P>
National Taiwan University in Taipei led other schools in 15
disciplines in terms of the number of articles it produced and in
16 disciplines in terms of the times their articles had been
cited, according to a survey released by the non-profit Higher
Education Evaluation &amp; Accreditation Council of Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
The survey, conducted by faculty from the Department of Library
and Information at National Taiwan University, counted the number
of articles local universities had turned out between 2002 and
2006 and had been published by journals collected by the
U.S.-based database Web of Science.
</P>
<P>
The authors of the survey found that National Taiwan University
led in physics, chemistry, mathematics, geoscience, chemical
engineering, civil engineering, clinical medicine, molecular
biology and genetics, biology, immunology and microbiology,
pharmacology and toxicology, psychiatry and psychology, botany
and zoology, agriculture, and ecology and environment.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile the National Chiao Tung University in Hsinchu City led
the pack in electrical engineering and computer science, National
Cheng Kung University in Tainan City led in mechanical
engineering and material science, National Yang Ming University
in Taipei led in the fields of neuroscience and behavior science.
</P>
<P>
Judged by the number of times their articles are cited, the
National Taiwan University ranked first in 16 disciplines, while
National Cheng Kung University in the fields of mechanical
engineering and material science, and National Yang Ming
University in the fields of neuroscience, behavior science,
psychiatry, and psychology.
</P>
